A 24-year-old man, Etounu Monday, has been arrested by operatives of the National Drug Law Enforcement Agency for attempting to export cannabis. According to a statement by the spokesperson of the agency, Femi Babafemi, the suspect was intercepted at the Nnamdi Azikiwe International Airport, Abuja on Monday 27th February during the outward clearance of Ethiopian Airline flight ET 950 while attempting to export 1.924kg of skunk concealed in cream tubes.